News Aggregator - Yahoo news /  Google news
the core objective is to pull data from millions of distinct web sources, normalize that data, group related articles into coherent "stories," and serve a personalized feed to users at scale.

Functional Requirements
Ingest articles from RSS feeds, sitemaps, and direct web scraping.
Deduplicate identical articles and cluster similar articles together (Topic Clustering).
Provide a real-time, personalized homepage based on user preferences and reading history.
Support text search across historical news articles.

Non-Functional Requirements
High Availability for Reads: Users expect instant feed generation.
Low Latency Ingestion: Breaking news should appear on the platform within minutes of publication.Scalability: 
System must handle $10^5+$ news sources and millions of concurrent active readers.

